<materialsCitation id="3B6B3C9BFFF8FF91FEB1FEF7FB78561D" box="[256,1205,350,376]" country="Brazil" location="Tijuca National Park" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Rio de Janeiro">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFF8FF91FEB1FEF7FEAF561D" box="[256,354,350,376]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">BRAZIL</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF8FF91FEDCFEF7FD82561D" box="[365,591,350,376]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Rio de Janeiro State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF8FF91FDEDFEF7FD32561D" box="[604,767,350,376]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<location id="8EDC601DFFF8FF91FCBAFEF7FC35561D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AA87D0FFF8FF91FF71FE93FC6B54B0:8EDC601DFFF8FF91FCBAFEF7FC35561D" box="[779,1016,350,376]" country="Brazil" name="Tijuca National Park" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" stateProvince="Rio de Janeiro">Tijuca National Park</location>
, Visitor’s Center
</materialsCitation>
; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFF8FF91FB73FEF7FAB1561D" box="[1218,1404,350,376]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" value="2021-01-18">18 January 2021</date>
; 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFF8FF91FA39FEF7FA50561D" box="[1416,1437,350,376]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">R</collectionCode>
. Dias. Host: Unidentified species (
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF8FF91FD87FED6FD6D56FF" box="[566,672,383,410]" class="Arachnida" family="Ctenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ctenidae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult female. The wasp straddled the recently captured, paralyzed wandering spider, examined it with her antennae as it laid dorsal side upward on the ground, and turned it onto its left side. She then detached the spider’s right legs at the trochanter-coxa joints using her mandibles. She also amputated the spider’s left legs at the trochanter-coxa joints. The wasp then ran across the ground, holding the delimbed host spider dorsal side upward while grasping the base of its chelicera with her mandibles. She stopped and paused, remaining atop her immobilized spider, on a green cement walkway (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF8FF91FB6AFD8EFA905524" author="Dias R." box="[1243,1373,551,577]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" refId="ref22648" refString="Dias R. 2021 a. Vespa prepara aranha capturada PNTijuca. Available at https: // www. youtube. com / watch? v = eg _ ajWnFm 4 Y &amp; feature = youtu. be. (Last accessed 10 February 2021)." type="url" year="2021">Dias 2021a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFF8FF91FEB1FDE0FDF15469" blockId="13.[191,1442,314,981]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<materialsCitation id="3B6B3C9BFFF8FF91FEB1FDE0FB785506" box="[256,1205,585,611]" country="Brazil" location="Tijuca National Park" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Rio de Janeiro">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFF8FF91FEB1FDE0FEAF5506" box="[256,354,585,611]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">BRAZIL</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF8FF91FEDCFDE0FD825506" box="[365,591,585,611]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Rio de Janeiro State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF8FF91FDEDFDE0FD325506" box="[604,767,585,611]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<location id="8EDC601DFFF8FF91FCBAFDE0FC355506" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AA87D0FFF8FF91FF71FE93FC6B54B0:8EDC601DFFF8FF91FCBAFDE0FC355506" box="[779,1016,585,611]" country="Brazil" name="Tijuca National Park" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" stateProvince="Rio de Janeiro">Tijuca National Park</location>
, Visitor’s Center
</materialsCitation>
; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFF8FF91FB73FDE0FAB15506" box="[1218,1404,585,611]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" value="2021-01-18">18 January 2021</date>
; 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFF8FF91FA39FDE0FA505506" box="[1416,1437,585,611]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">R</collectionCode>
. Dias. Host: Unidentified species (
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF8FF91FD80FDC3FD5655E0" box="[561,667,618,645]" class="Arachnida" family="Ctenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ctenidae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult female. The wasp ran up a vertical cement wall carrying an immobilized delimbed wandering spider, dorsal side upward, while grasping the base its chelicera with her mandibles. At the top she ran along the ledge to the end, then turned around and ran in the opposite direction to a tree growing against the wall. Without hesitating, the wasp with spider underneath continued running up the tree and out of sight (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF8FF91FE1CFD58FDFD5469" author="Dias R." box="[429,560,753,780]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" refId="ref22695" refString="Dias R. 2021 b. Vespa carregando aranha capturada PNTijuco. Available at https: // www. youtube. com / watch? v = GODxwLlA Yts &amp; feature = youtu. be. (Last accessed 10 February 2021." type="url" year="2021">Dias 2021b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFF8FF91FEB1FCBAFC6B54B0" blockId="13.[191,1442,314,981]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<materialsCitation id="3B6B3C9BFFF8FF91FEB1FCBAFC0C5449" box="[256,961,786,813]" country="Brazil" location="Alto da Boa Vista" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Rio de Janeiro">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFF8FF91FEB1FCBAFEAF5448" box="[256,354,787,813]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">BRAZIL</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF8FF91FEDAFCBBFD855448" box="[363,584,786,813]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Rio de Janeiro State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF8FF91FDE3FCBBFD3C5449" box="[594,753,786,812]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<location id="8EDC601DFFF8FF91FD4AFCBBFC0C5449" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AA87D0FFF8FF91FF71FE93FC6B54B0:8EDC601DFFF8FF91FD4AFCBBFC0C5449" box="[763,961,786,813]" country="Brazil" name="Alto da Boa Vista" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" stateProvince="Rio de Janeiro">Alto da Boa Vista</location>
</materialsCitation>
; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFF8FF91FC7AFCBAFBB75448" box="[971,1146,786,813]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" value="2017-10-08">8 October 2017</date>
; 1119; 
<materialsCitation id="3B6B3C9BFFF8FF91FB76FCBAFC6F54B0" collectionCode="R" country="Brazil" county="Dias. Host" location="She" municipality="The" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Rio de Janeiro">
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFF8FF91FB76FCBAFB115448" box="[1223,1244,787,813]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">R</collectionCode>
. 
<collectingCounty id="62DD4E4AFFF8FF91FB54FCBBFA905448" box="[1253,1373,786,813]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Dias. Host</collectingCounty>
:? 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF8FF91FAC0FCBAFEC3542A" class="Arachnida" family="Ctenidae" genus="Ctenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFF8FF91FAC0FCBAFF2A542B" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Ctenus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, adult or subadult female. 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BD8ACBCFFF8FF91FD88FC9DFDAE542B" box="[569,611,820,846]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">The</collectingMunicipality>
wasp examined the paralyzed wandering spider with her mouthparts and antennae as it laid dorsal side upward on the ground. 
<location id="8EDC601DFFF8FF91FCA0FCFFFCF45415" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AA87D0FFF8FF91FF71FE93FC6B54B0:8EDC601DFFF8FF91FCA0FCFFFCF45415" box="[785,825,854,880]" country="Brazil" county="Dias. Host" municipality="The" name="She" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" stateProvince="Rio de Janeiro">She</location>
then grasped its right chelicera with her mandibles and attempted to pull it backwards across the ground. 
<location id="8EDC601DFFF8FF91FD5EFCDEFCDC54F4" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AA87D0FFF8FF91FF71FE93FC6B54B0:8EDC601DFFF8FF91FD5EFCDEFCDC54F4" box="[751,785,887,913]" country="Brazil" county="Dias. Host" municipality="The" name="All" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" stateProvince="Rio de Janeiro">All</location>
of the spider’s legs were intact (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF8FF91FBC5FCDEFB3854F4" author="Dias R." box="[1140,1269,887,913]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" refId="ref22738" refString="Dias R. 2021 c. Spider Wasps (Family Pompilidae). Available at https: // www. inaturalist. org / observations / 70005895; https: // www. youtube. com / watch? v = - N-NJNFJYQU (Last accessed 23 February 2021)." type="url" year="2021">Dias 2021c</bibRefCitation>
). A subsequent very short video shows the spider with some of its legs amputated at the coxa-trochanter joints and lying on the ground (
<location id="8EDC601DFFF8FF91FE90FC13FE9B54B1" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AA87D0FFF8FF91FF71FE93FC6B54B0:8EDC601DFFF8FF91FE90FC13FE9B54B1" box="[289,342,954,980]" country="Brazil" county="Dias. Host" municipality="The" name="Dias" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" stateProvince="Rio de Janeiro">Dias</location>
2019; 
<location id="8EDC601DFFF8FF91FE2FFC13FE1E54B1" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AA87D0FFF8FF91FF71FE93FC6B54B0:8EDC601DFFF8FF91FE2FFC13FE1E54B1" box="[414,467,954,980]" country="Brazil" county="Dias. Host" municipality="The" name="Dias" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" stateProvince="Rio de Janeiro">Dias</location>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF8FF91FE6CFC13FDB054B1" box="[477,637,954,980]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<location id="8EDC601DFFF8FF91FD36FC13FD0654B1" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AA87D0FFF8FF91FF71FE93FC6B54B0:8EDC601DFFF8FF91FD36FC13FD0654B1" box="[647,715,954,980]" country="Brazil" county="Dias. Host" municipality="The" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" stateProvince="Rio de Janeiro">Brazil</location>
, 2021 pers. comm)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
